main event: An oval object changing colors from rosy pink to blue was sighted near Poulsbo, Washington on June 22, 1955.
interesting points: The object was described as oval with changing colors between rosy pink and blue., Three lights were observed: two small and one large., The sighting lasted approximately one hour., Weather conditions were clear with unlimited visibility., Investigators concluded the object was likely caused by weather balloons due to its movement and duration of sighting.
sighted object: oval shaped object with flashing lights
witness description: Mrs. Waghorn, GCC Chief Observer, Poulsbo, Washington
